                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the east wall of the central shrine in the Raṅganātha temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Palaeographically this inscription can be assigned to the 15th century A.D.,</p>						
                            
                            <p>It mentions that the flooring of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> was made by Uḍaiyār Maṇavāḷa Āḻvāṉ Taṇḍadanāṭṭu-Brahmādarāyaṉ of Neṟkuṉṟam <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Rājachūḍāmaṇinallūr in Viḍāl-paṟṟu.</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
